'''''The Maiden''''' (''Die Jungfrau'') is a painting by the Austrian painter [[Gustav Klimt]] painted in year 1913. Currently it's stored in the [[National Gallery in Prague]], [http://context.reverso.net/translation/english-russian/Czech+Republic][[Czech Republic]].

== Description ==
The abundance of the flowers in the painting symbolizes the evolution into womanhood. The painting depicts seven women that are interlacing. Each woman represents a particular life stage. The painting touches on various topics of human life, such as love, sexuality and regeneration that are depicted in cyclical shape.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.klimt.com/en/gallery/women/klimt-die-jungfrau-1913.ihtml|title=Die Jungfrauen 1913|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>

